{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":130371,"duration_api_ms":129818,"num_turns":28,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"78a1e813-cb3d-4501-aa5a-d01fcc86ac69","total_cost_usd":1.12336925,"usage":{"input_tokens":18,"cache_creation_input_tokens":74641,"cache_read_input_tokens":1066346,"output_tokens":4944,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":74641,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":18,"outputTokens":4944,"cacheReadInputTokens":1066346,"cacheCreationInputTokens":74641,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.12336925,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 73 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored)","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","model.rs: TaskRunEntry has all required fields — milestone_id (line 275), bead_id (278), project_id (280), run_id (282), plan_hash (285), outcome (288), outcome_detail (290), started_at (293), finished_at (296) — all new optional fields use serde(default, skip_serializing_if) for backward compatibility","model.rs: Shared helpers now centralized — same_attempt (line 301), merge_attempt_entries (line 312), collapse_task_run_attempts (line 336) all live in model.rs. The old duplicates (task_runs_same_attempt, merge_task_run_attempt, normalize_task_runs in service.rs and same_attempt, merge_attempt_rows, collapse_runs_for_bead in fs.rs) are fully removed. Both service.rs (lines 140, 389) and fs.rs (lines 2306, 2318, 2625, 2702) import and use the shared model helpers. This addresses amendment fr-4-65a16a24.","service.rs: update_task_run (line 608) uses `snapshot.updated_at = snapshot.updated_at.max(finished_at).max(event_timestamp)` ensuring snapshot timestamps never regress on replay. Similarly record_bead_start (line 478) uses `snapshot.updated_at = snapshot.updated_at.max(now).max(started_at)`. This addresses amendment fr-4-54b5dd71.","service.rs: record_bead_start (lines 392-423) now checks for existing matching running entries before appending, reusing canonical open attempts when found. The start_retry_with_same_run_id_is_idempotent test (line 1900) verifies: first start fails after lineage append, retry reuses the existing running row (runs remain 1), snapshot is consistent, journal has exactly 1 start event. This addresses amendment fr-4-013c9cb2.","fs.rs: update_task_run (lines 2544-2575) now handles multiple exact run_id matches by selecting the terminal one if available, or the first running one, and merging duplicates — rather than rejecting as ambiguous. Test duplicate_running_rows_with_same_run_id_can_be_finalized (line 2003) verifies two running rows with same run_id are consolidated to 1 row after finalization. This further addresses fr-4-013c9cb2.","fs.rs: unique_terminal_replay_match (line 2360) enables replaying completions against legacy two-row NDJSON data. When open_matches is empty (legacy start is superseded, terminal already exists), it finds the unique terminal entry whose every sibling is a legacy start for it. Both no-run_id paths (lines 2592-2605) and with-run_id paths (lines 2519-2532) call this fallback. Test legacy_terminal_replay_without_run_id_repairs_milestone_state (line 1540) verifies: legacy running+terminal paired rows can be replayed with backfill, snapshot transitions from stale Active to Ready, journal gets exactly 1 BeadFailed event. This addresses amendment fr-4-0195eaea.","service.rs: reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage (line 135) rebuilds all counters from canonical lineage, transitions Active→Ready when no active beads remain (line 187-188), and validates via validate_semantics (line 173-186) that Active requires active_bead and terminal status forbids active_bead.","service.rs: Journal deduplication via journal_contains_event (lines 220-230) prevents double-counting on replay for both start (line 486) and completion (line 619) paths.","model.rs: same_attempt (line 301-309) uses run_id matching when both sides have run_id, falls back to started_at comparison for legacy entries without run_id — correctly handling both modern and legacy data.","model.rs: merge_attempt_entries (line 312-333) enhanced from prior version to also take min(started_at) and handle finished_at propagation, making it more robust for duplicate-row merging."],"findings_or_gaps":["All four final-review amendments (fr-4-54b5dd71, fr-4-65a16a24, fr-4-0195eaea, fr-4-013c9cb2) have been addressed with code changes and regression tests in this round.","The outstanding risk noted by the implementor — that completion still spans lineage, snapshot, and journal writes without a cross-file transaction — remains. However, all three write paths (start, completion, update) are now designed so that replaying the same operation repairs drift, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs line 582) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run. A more specific error variant would be semantically cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior review.","The FailFirstJournalAppend mock (line 666) is a well-designed test helper that simulates start-side journal failure to exercise the idempotent retry path. The test verifies the full lifecycle: failed start → retry → successful completion.","The unique_terminal_replay_match helper (fs.rs line 2360) correctly identifies a terminal entry that is the sole non-legacy-start match, enabling backward-compatible replay. The filter logic (is_legacy_start_for at line 2310) is clean and uses the shared same_attempt helper."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"1b3cfdf7-925e-4adf-96f5-28bc1c24142f"}
